'''Paris''' is the capital and largest city of France, on the river Seine in the country's north. It has been a major European centre of finance, diplomacy, fashion, and the arts for centuries.

The city is celebrated for landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower, Notre-Dame, and the Louvre, and hosts world-leading art collections at the [[Musée d'Orsay]], the Centre Pompidou, and other institutions.
